<TITLE> Man held for murder of BCL activist in Dhaka </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 13 (bdnews24.com)  Rapid Action Battalion have arrested one suspect in connection with the murder of Bangladesh Chhatra League leader ABM Faruk, who was shot dead in the capital on Friday night. Thirty-five year old 'Shahdat', a restaurant manager by profession, was arrested at a house in Manikdi near Dhaka Cantonment in the early hours of Saturday. RAB official Maj Sarwar told bdnews24.com Shahdat confessed his connection with the murder of Faruk, the son of a former army officer. Faruk, president of BCL's Cantonment Thana chapter and also head of its Ward 15 unit, was shot at the Manikdi Adorsho Bidyaniketan sportsground, beside Shahdat's restaurant, at around 9:30pm on Friday. BCL claimed that Jamaat-e-Islami and its student wing Islami Chhatra Shibir were involved in the killing. bdnew
